text_unprocessed: Putative QTL with a period-lengthening effect of about 1 h
Mutants are defective in leaf and inflorescence meristem. Cauline leaves are small and twisted in appearance. Meristem is smaller in diameter and terminates early so the plants produce fewer flowers.
Loss of function mutants have reduced internode length.

Loss of function mutants have reduced internode length and smaller leaves. May be involved in cell elongation. acl3-1 allele can be suppressed by growth at 28C. In mutant plants, expression of endoxyloglucan transferase is decreased.
Temperature-sensitive gene required for normal shoot apical meristem function
Mutant shows an altered pattern of auxin-responsive gene expression and has a short, bushy growth habit with pale leaves and cotyledons
Involved in the regulation of gene expression in response to IAA.
A genetic locus involved in regulation of glutathione S-transferase 1.
A genetic locus involved in chloroplast or chlorophyll development.
alf3-1 is defective in the maturation of lateral roots

a genetic locus involved in response to aluminum. Lines carrying recessive mutations appear to accumulate less aluminum and callose than wild type. This locus is mapped to chromosome 5 near SSLP marker nga151.
ANDANTE, QTL for circadian period.
A genetic locus involved in anthocyanin production. An EMS mutant lacks anthocyanin in vegetative tissues.

A late-flowering locus isolated from the Sy-O ecotype that maps on chromosome 5, between the ms1 and ttg visible markers in a genomic interval defined by the MYJ24 and MKD15 BACs. Phenotype of the dominant allele requires the presence of another dominant allele, FLC. ART1 activates FLC which is a floral repressor.
partially divided guard cell
Identified in a screen using segregation distortion to uncover gametophyte mutations. Pollen grains from heterozygous BOD1 plants are abnormal  and embryo sacs are occasionally absent.
Identified in a screen using segregation distortion to uncover gametophyte mutations. Pollen grains from heterozygous BOD2 plants plants are abnormal  and embryo sacs are occasionally absent.

Both male and female gametophytic defective 3.Identified in a EMS screen using segregation distortion to uncover gametophyte mutations. Pollen grains from heterozygous BOD3 plants are abnormal and embryo sacs are occasionally absent.
cauliflower mosaic virus resistance1
ch5 mutant is characterized by chlorophyll deficiency
Paler green embryos and green-yellow plants
Putative nitrate reductase.
Nitrate assimilation
A genetic locus required for the synthesis of a molybdenum cofactor (MoCo) required for nitrate reductase activity.
A genetic locus involved in chlorophyll development. Mutants are pale green. This mutation delays flowering time but not leaf number.
semi-dwarf mutant
lines carrying recessive mutations in this genetic locus are compact and semi-dwarf.
dwarf mutant compacta 3 negatively regulates the phytochrome A signalling pathway
Regulator of expression of pathogenesis-related (PR) genes. Participates in signal transduction pathways involved in plant defense (systemic acquired resistance --SAR).
Mutant is insensitive to cesium, has potassium uptake defect.
involved in root hair development, cell expansion, cell division, cell polarity. cud-1 allele is dominant and male-sterile, X-ray induced in Col.
Required for the execution of cytokinesis throughout the shoot. Effects are seen in both mature vegetative and reproductive organs.

Some inflorescence internodes lacking, aerial rosettes, shoot apical meristem consumed in floral structures after about 10 nodes, low apical dominance, distorted leaf morphology, pale green, abnormal stamen development
Mutations in this gene have aberrant regulation of CAB3 gene expression, they overexpress CAB3 in the dark.
mutant allowing derepression of CAB expression in dark-grown seedlings.
dth mutants are deregulated in the control of expression of CEVI-1 gene.
Genetic locus involved in a late step of brassinosteroid biosynthesis.  Maps to the bottom of chromosome 1.
Required for resistance to some pathogenic bacteria. Mutants are more susceptible to Peronospora parasitica and Pseudomonas syringae but not to Erysiphe orontii.
Mutant has compact rosette and serrated leaves.  Involved in disease resistance.
enhanced disease susceptibility 9
a genetic locus involved in silencing of transgenes. Mutants carrying a recessive allele enhances the silencing of 35S::rolB transgene in Arabidopsis.
